text: trooperjoe73 Fyi, before they made the Harvey Birdman cartoon series that was shown on late night cartoon network, years before that there was actually a serious Birdman cartoon that was on Saturday mornings in the late 70's-early 80's shown right before or after the Superfriends with Superman, Batman, Robin, Aquaman, Wonder Woman, Green Lantern and the Wonder Twins. Birdman was a great superhero and he had a falcon or hawk named Avenger as his sidekick. When they did the comedy version it was pretty funny satire but I was bummed out just a little because I loved the serious version as a kid. But I can't wait to see this movie, should be a riot.

" washed-up actor who once played an iconic superhero must overcome his ego and family trouble as he mounts a Broadway play in a bid to reclaim his past glory"  BIRDMAN is a fictional superhero, the actor who played him is stuck in his past. So much so, that he likely thinks he's the character he played on the big screen.  I can't wait.

"only smart people can see these clothes" " only smart people like this movie"  hint: there's fucking nothing.  throwing random shit into a movie and not giving it an explanation leading critics to come to indirect conclusions does not make a movie "smarter". Just like Hurt Locker, it was over-hyped. Guy goes to war, kills some people, comes home, has PTSD and has a hard time adjusting back to normal life with family and friends. Nothing that spectacular happens. Black Hawk Down was a 1000 times better and more entertaining than Hurt Locker and Sniper and won no major Oscars.
